Comment:
Game against lanlee i felt was rather interesting and an exciting game for me. I was quite down throughout most part of this game because of how well he was playing in our other game, but was able to overcome this. 

He kicked off with d4
d5
c4,pawn sacrifice for classic pawn centre, a novel beginning in many a players game
Nf6, declined variation
c takes
f takes
e4, a good opening i admit
knight back to b6
queen out early, lots of players avoid this. maybe this will become a weakness
e6, for castling it also protects d5 in variations an annoying spacial cramp for black
be3, eyeing down b6 maybe to wreck my pawns
bb4 check, the king is fairly exposed, the purpose of this move is time rather than anything else
bd2, a trade off perhaps. what did white leave behind?
queen takes d4!
bxb4
queen takes..check
nc3,this allows the piece to be pinned. but still allows castling
queen takes b2.
rook b1
queen a3, my queen can run out of space very quickly, a retreat first to a3 to allow more options
